title: 2013 - The Year In Christian Music (Bundle 42)
description:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
2013 - THE YEAR IN CHRISTIAN MUSIC
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

After spending the last few days torrenting all of those 118 Gaither albums, it's kind of nice to get back on track with more of these Year In Christian Music bundles.

Once again, for anyone interested, I might break down this 42nd bundle into 7vnseal, The Ambassador, Flame, and Trilogy for anyone wanting Hip-Hop/Rap.  There's a lot of Gospel (and some Southern Gospel) including All Sons And Daughters, The Collingsworth Family, Crist Family, Donald Lawrence, Laura Story, and Mountain Faith.  There's even a Bluegrass album from The Bankesters that you might want to check out.  If Alternative music is your interest, then be sure to get a copy of Dustin Kensrue, Josiah James, and Thomas Dybdahl.  Folk music?  How about Guthrie.  Are you looking for some Praise & Worship today?  How about Hillsong, Jake Cantrell, Kate Hurley, and Women Of Faith.  Jacob Wright might be considered Rock.  And John Tibbs might be considered Indie.  After several Christmas albums in my last 41st bundle, there are only two in this 42nd bundle.  You can choose from either Jonathan Butler, and Paul Baloche.  And there are three Pop albums available including Martin Smith, Natalie Grant, and Press Play.  If you're looking for Singer-Songwriter then consider Nick Law, and Steve Grand.  There's a great upbeat Acapella album from Vive.  And rounding it all out once again, if you're a Metal fan, you're going to want to get the newest Wolves At The Gate.

Bundle 42 includes the following 33 releases, bringing out total shared for the year up to 1,173 titles...
